{"cursor":"41731","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"\n\n{{Infobox VG character |name = Sonic the Hedgehog |width = |image = |caption =\nModern and classic Sonic designs, as they appear in [[Sonic Generations]]\n|firstgame = *Rad Mobile (Cameo appearance) *Sonic the Hedgehog (as playable\ncharacter) |series = [[Sonic the Hedgehog series|Sonic the Hedgehog]] |creator =\nYuji Naka Naoto Åshima |artist= 'Video games' Naoto Åshima\n(Sonic the Hedgehog) 'Artwork' Akira Watanabe\n(Sonic the Hedgehog) Yuji Uekawa (Sonic Adventure, Latest release: Sonic Generations) |voiceactor = 'Video games' Keiko\nUtoku (Sonic CD) Ryan Drummond (1998-2004) Jason Griffith (2005-2010) Roger Craig Smith (2010-\nPresent) 'Cartoons' Jaleel White ([[Adventures of Sonic\nthe Hedgehog|AoStH]], [[Sonic the Hedgehog (TV series)|SatAM]], [[Sonic\nUnderground]]) Samuel Vincent ([[Sonic Underground]]\n(singing voice) 'Anime' Martin Burke () Jason Griffith ([[Sonic X]]) |japanactor = 'Video games' Takeshi Kusao (1993) Junichi Kanemaru (1998-\npresent) Tomokazu Seki (Werehog form, [[Sonic\nUnleashed]]) 'Cartoons' Kappei Yamaguchi (AoStH and\nSatAM) Keiko Toda (Sonic Underground) 'Anime' Masami Kikuchi (Sonic OVA) Junichi Kanemaru (Sonic\nX) |inuniverse = {{Sonic character |nickname = The Blue Blur |species =\nHedgehog |likes = Chili dogs |skills = Supersonic speed (running)  Super transformation }}}}\n\n, trademarked Sonic The Hedgehog, is a title character and\nthe protagonist of the ''Sonic the Hedgehog'' series released by Sega, as well\nas in numerous spin-off comics, 4 animated shows and an animated OVA. The first\ngame was released on June 23, 1991, to provide Sega with a mascot to rival\nNintendo's flagship character Mario (see 1991 in video gaming). Davis, Cameron and Shoemaker, Brad\n[http://uk.gamespot.com/gamespot/features/video/hist_sonic/index.html The\nHistory of Sonic the Hedgehog], GameSpot. Retrieved June 16, 2008. Since\nthen, Sonic has become one of the world's best-known video game characters, with\nhis series having sold more than 80 million copies. http://www.sonicstadium.org/wp-\ncontent/uploads/2010/02/4ihg.jpg In 2005, Sonic was one of the first game\ncharacter inductees into the Walk of Game, alongside Mario and Link.\n\nWhile many individuals at Sega had a hand in Sonic's creation, programmer Yuji\nNaka and artist Naoto Åshima are generally credited with the creation of the\ncharacter, a blue 15-year-old anthropomorphic\nhedgehog, who has the ability to run at supersonic speeds and the ability to\ncurl into a ball, primarily to attack enemies. This is a major part of the\ngameplay of the series.\n","linknr":714,"url":"Sonic_the_Hedgehog_(character)","recorded":1364111206,"links":["//en.wikipedia.org/apple-touch-icon.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/favicon/wikipedia.ico","/w/opensearch_desc.php","//en.wikipedia.org/w/api.php?action=rsd","//creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/","/w/index.php?title=Special:RecentChanges&feed=atom","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=ext.gadget.DRN-wizard%2CReferenceTooltips%2Ccharinsert%2Cteahouse%7Cext.wikihiero%7Cmediawiki.legacy.commonPrint%2Cshared%7Cmw.PopUpMediaTransform%7Cskins.vector&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=site&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=startup&only=scripts&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/geoiplookup","//meta.wikimedia.org","#mw-head","#p-search","/wiki/Hedgehog_signaling_pathway","/wiki/Sonic_hedgehog","/wiki/Wikipedia:Protection_policy#semi","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/fc/Padlock-silver.svg/20px-Padlock-silver.svg.png","/wiki/Sonic_the_Hedgehog_series","/wiki/File:Sonic_modern_and_classic_designs.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/f/f4/Sonic_modern_and_classic_designs.png","/wiki/Sonic_Generations","/wiki/Rad_Mobile","/wiki/Cameo_appearance","/wiki/Soni